cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 

- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper describes the implementation of a software package for solving hyperbolic PDEs using finite volume methods. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses a parallel, adaptive, multi-block algorithm for explicit integration of time-dependent partial differential equations on two-dimensional Cartesian grids. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on parallel partitioning of grids and parallel ghost-filling algorithm to ensure valid values in ghost regions. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the application of the algorithm to solve problems on a variety of geometries including the cubed sphere. 
- cs.SC (Scientific Computing): The paper describes a software package for solving hyperbolic PDEs using finite volume methods and discusses its application to solve problems on a variety of geometries.
